%U A244324 549754241024,8796086730752,140737463189504,1166333691001023,144115187270549504,36472996363223648799,374444425895728906239999
%N A244324 Numbers m such that sigma(m) == (m+1)/2 (mod m+1).
%C A244324 Also, numbers m such that m+1 divides antisigma(m) = A024816(m). Corresponding values of antisigma(m)/(m+1): 0, 0, 6, 8, 50, 102, 230, 323, 510, 974, 1486, 9678, ...
%C A244324 Also, numbers m such that A244325(m) = floor(antisigma(m) / m) = antisigma(m) mod m = A229110(m).
%C A244324 Terms with quotients q = 2*sigma(m)/(m+1): q=1 corresponds to {1}, q=2 corresponds to {2}, q=3 corresponds to A063906, q=4 corresponds to even terms of A088831. No terms with q>=5 are known. - _Max Alekseyev_, Jul 09 2026
%e A244324 Antisigma(19359) = 187366080 = 9678*19359 + 9678.
%o A244324 (Magma) [n: n in [1..1000000] | u eq 0 where u is (Floor((((n*(n+1)) div 2 - SumOfDivisors(n)) div n))) - (((((n*(n+1)) div 2)-SumOfDivisors(n)) mod (n)))];
%o A244324 (PARI) isok(n) = my(as = n*(n+1)/2 - sigma(n)); (as\n == as % n); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 26 2014
%Y A244324 Subsequences: A063906, even terms of A088831.
%Y A244324 Cf. A024816, A045768, A244325, A229110.
%K A244324 nonn,hard,changed
%O A244324 1,2
